data.description: Welcome to 206 Streams Way! As you enter this beautiful home you will appreciate the thoughtful floor plan, vaulted ceilings throughout, and natural light - with large windows all around! The back deck overlooks a private back yard and creek, where you can enjoy watching wildlife come to drink. This home feels cozy, spacious, and practical. Plenty of closet space! New roof in 2022, and 2 new HVAC units in 2022!!Crawl space is very clean, tall, and includes a full vapor barrier. Convenient walk in attic from the second level. This home is in a prime location! Situated in a quiet neighborhood - with grocery stores, Walgreens, and a few dining options less than 5 minutes away. 10 minutes to Clemson Blvd for all of your shopping and dining needs! 10 minutes to public lake access for swimming, paddle boarding, playground, and picnicking. 10 minutes to highway 85, and less than 50 minutes to Greenville.   Closer look: The ideal floor plan! On the main level, you have your master suite with "his and her" closets, beautiful windows, vaulted ceiling, and private bathroom. The spacious master bathroom includes a soaking tub, separate shower, linen closet, and plenty of counter space. The laundry room is located close to the master, and also acts as a mudroom connecting the garage to the home. Half bath is on the main level. This home has a large, appointed eat-in dining area off the kitchen, PLUS a formal dining room in the front of the home. This allows you to choose if you want two dining areas or use the front dining room as an office or sitting area! The second bedroom, third bedroom, bonus room, and second full bath are all on the second level, creating a nice split floor plan from the master and main living space. The third bedroom and upstairs bathroom have vaulted ceilings, and the loft overlooks the living room creating an open spacious feel. Extra wide driveway to fit 3 cars side by side. Schedule your showing today!
